Text: Great to see Chicago’s historic mayoral race between two highly qualified candidates. Congrats to our next mayor Lori Lightfoot—and Toni Preckwinkle campaigned hard and did us proud. I know that with our city’s heart and Lori’s leadership Chicago’s best days are still ahead.

Text: Of course @MichelleObama’s my wife so I’m a little biased here. But she also happens to be brilliant funny wise – one of a kind. This book tells her quintessentially American story. I love it because it faithfully reflects the woman I have loved for so long.pic.twitter.com/X0i9jja4TE

Text: Michelle and I are heartbroken for everybody who’s lost so much in California and grateful for the heroism of the firefighters who’ve been risking their lives around the clock to save others. Please do what you can to help our fellow Americans in need:https://nyti.ms/2DdQB3c
Author: Obama

Text: To all our veterans and your families: thank you. There's no tribute that can truly match the magnitude of your service and sacrifice. But all of us can do our best to live up to the American values of service responsibility generosity and citizenship that you helped defend.
Author: Obama

Text: Congratulations to everybody who showed up and participated in our democracy in record numbers yesterday. The change we need won’t come from one election alone – but it is a start. Last night voters across the country started it.pic.twitter.com/gNk4WkeJUn
Author: Obama

Text: Today is the day. Today it’s your turn to raise your voice to change the course of this country for the better. So make it count. Get out there and vote. Go to http://IWillVote.com  or call 833-336-VOTE to confirm where you can vote and check voting hours.pic.twitter.com/6xdMbKhwkr
Author: Obama

Text: When you vote you have the power to protect voting rights. To make sure our criminal justice system treats everyone equally under the law. To strengthen laws that protect women in the workplace from harassment – and make sure they’re paid equally.
Author: Obama

Text: When we've been at such crossroads before Americans have made the right choice. Not because we sat back and waited for history to happen -- but because we marched and mobilized and voted. We made history happen.
Author: Obama

Text: Tomorrow’s elections might be the most important of our lifetimes. The health care of millions is on the ballot. Making sure working families get a fair shake is on the ballot. The character of our country is on the ballot.
Author: Obama

Text: Your vote can decide the health care of millions. Your voice can determine the character of our country. You have power — use it! Text: We grieve for the Americans murdered in Pittsburgh. All of us have to fight the rise of anti-Semitism and hateful rhetoric against those who look love or pray differently. And we have to stop making it so easy for those who want to harm the innocent to get their hands on a gun.

Text: Thank you God Bless you and may He forever bless these United States of America.
Author: Obama

Text: We must act knowing that our work will be imperfect.
Author: Obama

Text: We cannot mistake absolutism for principle or substitute spectacle for politics or treat name-calling as reasoned debate.
Author: Obama

Text: Decisions are upon us and we cannot afford delay.
Author: Obama

Text: Our journey is not complete until all our children know that they are cared for and cherished and always safe from harm.
Author: Obama

Text: Our journey is not complete until we find a better way to welcome the immigrants who still see America as a land of opportunity.
Author: Obama

Text: Our journey is not complete until no citizen is forced to wait for hours to exercise the right to vote.
Author: Obama

Text: Our journey is not complete until our wives our mothers and daughters can earn a living equal to their efforts.
Author: Obama

Text: We the people declare today that the most evident of truths—that all of us are created equal—is the star that guides us still.
Author: Obama

Text: We will respond to the threat of climate change knowing that the failure to do so would betray our children and future generations.
Author: Obama

Text: We the people still believe that our obligations as Americans are not just to ourselves but to all posterity.
Author: Obama

Text: We do not believe that in this country freedom is reserved for the lucky or happiness for the few.
Author: Obama

Text: America’s possibilities are limitless for we possess all the qualities that this world without boundaries demands.
Author: Obama

Text: This generation of Americans has been tested by crises that steeled our resolve and proved our resilience.
Author: Obama

Text: Now more than ever we must do these things together as one nation and one people.
Author: Obama
